reviews.text: Michelin recommended, one of the best Chinese restaurants in Hong Kong on dim sum, roast duck and roast pigs.
One of the best dim sum I've ever had. The roast pork and their fried tofu were two of my favourite dishes. The chicken soup was good for the soul too! MUST TRY!

Definitely not worth your time if you're looking for good sharkfin soup. Expensive yet tasteless. 1/10

Salted fish fried rice was 2/10

Poor hygiene by the staff, the waiter was cooking the Claypot rice, the rice dropped on the table, moreover, she used her hand to pick it up and served it for customers. 

Overall 1/10. Don't make the same mistake.
Good variety of Dim Sum
Delicious food, clean, pleasant atmosphere.

result.name: Fu Sing Seafood Restaurant

reviews.text:
Fu Sing Seafood Restaurant in Causeway Bay, Hong Kong is a well established joint in HK.

I came to Fu Sing Seafood Restaurant for brunch  because of my Auntie who lives in North Point.  She is an old timer that fancies good quality food and decor.  

The Dim Sum here is very fresh and they have a huge variety of it.  They always put  together different kinds of food so there is a different way to make the same old boring Dim Sums into something new and happening.  

In order to maintain it's clientele, most well known Hong Kong restaurants have a signature dishes. 

While i wish i had not forgotten the signature dish of Fu Sing Seafood Restaurant, so I may pass the information on.  The food is fresh, and of good quality, and i enjoyed the meal.  

Pleasant decor to seat  the guests in comfort.  The tables and chairs are placed spaciously apart so there is elbow room.

The staff is friendly and quite pleasant.  The restaurant is kept clean and tidy.
We always have to visit this resto for good pork char sui in Causeway bay

Tonight my mum treated us some nice dinner with her brother. It rained rather heavily this evening. We waited for the rain to stop before heading to the restaurant. We didn't want to have to travel far, so we decided to eat nearby the hotel. This was my first time to this restaurant. My brother did the ordered. He did a great job in ordering the food for us. 

Overall the dishes were okay, nothing very special. There were two outstanding dishes for me; the fish head and the salted egg prawns. The other dishes was just okay. The fish in the claypot was very fishy. 

The service was rather bad. They were not very attentive at all given that there were not a lot of customers in the restaurant.

I'm not sure if I would wanna come back here again. My brother mentioned that this is a rather well known restaurant in Hong Kong. Hmmm....🤔
excellent food. consistent quality. attentive staff.
Good roast pork. Rice roll and dim sum
